library(ggplot2)
library(ggplot2movies)

Histogram

# alpha for transparency
ggplot(movies, aes(x=rating)) + geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.1, color = 'Red', fill = 'pink', alpha = 0.4) + xlab('Movie Rating') + ylab('Count') + ggtitle('Histogram of Ratings')

# get histogram with fill set to count of ratings
ggplot(movies, aes(x=rating)) + geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.1, aes(fill=..count..)) + xlab('Movie Rating') + ylab('Count') + ggtitle('Histogram of Ratings')

Scatterplots

df <- mtcars

#to define shapes and colors with respect to variables, use aes inside geom_point.
ggplot(df, aes(x = wt, y = mpg)) + geom_point(aes(shape=factor(cyl),color=factor(cyl)), size=5,alpha = 0.8)

#Change color of points in default geom_point by using scale_color_gradient
ggplot(df, aes(x = wt, y = mpg)) + geom_point(aes(color=hp), size=5) + scale_color_gradient(low = 'blue', high = 'red') 

df <- mpg

#use position to change layout of barplots dodge/fill
ggplot(df, aes(x= class)) + geom_bar(aes(fill=drv), position = 'dodge')

Boxplots

df <- mtcars
#boxplots need categorical values on the x axis
#Change coordinate by using coord_flip()
ggplot(df, aes(x= factor(cyl),y = mpg)) + geom_boxplot(aes(fill=factor(cyl))) + coord_flip()

2 variable plotting

#install.packages("hexbin")
ggplot(movies, aes(x= year,y = rating)) + geom_bin2d()

ggplot(movies, aes(x=year, y = rating)) + geom_bin2d() + scale_fill_gradient(high = 'red', low = 'green')

#

ggplot(movies, aes(x=year, y = rating)) + geom_hex() + scale_fill_gradient(high = 'red', low = 'green')

Coordinates and Facets

ggplot(mpg, aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + geom_point() + coord_cartesian(xlim = c(1,4), ylim = c(15,30))

#Facets
ggplot(mpg, aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + geom_point() + facet_grid(cyl ~ .)

ggplot(mpg, aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + geom_point() + facet_grid(cyl ~ drv)
